// @test: typecheck-fail
// @tier: all
// @level: L0
// @tags: modules, mount, braced-import, error-reporting, T0242
// @expected-error: E402
// @description: A genuinely missing module in a braced mount must still
// fail LOUD with E402.
//
// T0242 negative pin -- the guard on the fix. Making braced TYPE mounts
// fall back to the archive type metadata must NOT turn a real typo into
// silence. The fallback fires only when the type authority actually
// materialises a descriptor for the requested ITEM name; when it does
// not, E402 stands.
//
// Both the module path AND the item name below are nonexistent, which
// is the shape a user typo takes. Note the archive keys types by the
// enclosing archive module rather than by leaf `.vr` file, so a mount
// path that differs only in a leaf segment the archive does not
// preserve is NOT distinguishable here by design -- this pin asserts
// the loudness the architecture can actually guarantee.

mount core.net.definitely_not_a_real_module.{NoSuchTypeAnywhere};

fn main() -> Int {
    0
}
